On the other hand, the cars with historical value may be re-authorised, even if they have been de-registered after difficult authorities.
Cost estimate of the workshop in four steps
With the Auda-Taller tool, the company Audatex ensures that the user receives a cost estimate in just four steps:identification of the vehicle, search of the spare part, creation and creation of a cost estimate.
The ease of handling of these systems is a fundamental condition, especially to convince the older professionals, who are usually more or less opposed to the use of these new computer techniques.
The database includes 1,034 vehicles, 666 of which are passenger cars, 109 off-road cars, 137 motorcycles, 78 small transporters and 44 trucks.
Of course you need a computer with Internet connection for use.
After the model to be repaired has been identified by the chassis number, a graphic of the respective model appears and then the required replacement part is selected.
The user can include variables such as the price for working hours, surcharges or discounts and thereafter can have the cost estimate printed out and passed on to his customers.
However, AudaTaller is not a tool for evaluation such as AudaPlus, but rather a reference catalogue.
The main difference between the two systems is that the workshop-oriented work does not include estimated working hours.
The cost of using this tool is 350 euros a year, an amount that the customer can pay without further delay.
Currently, the company Audatex is working to offer these images in three-dimensional format.
This is an innovation that car mechanics have been waiting for a long time, as you can choose a door with it for example and then turn the picture completely to look at the inside.
